From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenWrt <noreply@openwrt.org>
Date: Sat, 19 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] net: airoha: ppe: fix foe flow bucket lookup for empty hw
 entries

When a PPE hardware entry is in INVALID state (cleared or never
committed), its packet fields are zeroed. Computing the hash from
these fields via airoha_ppe_foe_get_entry_hash() produces a wrong
bucket index, so the hlist walk cannot find the matching SW flow
entry to clean up.

Use the original hash parameter (which is the correct hash from
the skb) when the HW entry state is INVALID.

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt <noreply@openwrt.org>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
index 000000000..000000001 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/airoha/airoha_ppe.c
@@ -939,7 +939,10 @@
 		goto unlock;
 
 	state = FIELD_GET(AIROHA_FOE_IB1_BIND_STATE, hwe->ib1);
-	index = airoha_ppe_foe_get_entry_hash(ppe, hwe);
+	if (state == AIROHA_FOE_STATE_INVALID)
+		index = hash;
+	else
+		index = airoha_ppe_foe_get_entry_hash(ppe, hwe);
 	hlist_for_each_entry_safe(e, n, &ppe->foe_flow[index], list) {
 		if (e->type == FLOW_TYPE_L2_SUBFLOW) {
 			state = FIELD_GET(AIROHA_FOE_IB1_BIND_STATE, hwe->ib1);
